DescUsage: <<
Installation from source:

see installation instructions in Makefile.
Basically, you will need a C compiler and make/gnumake.
You need yorick in your executable path.

You will need also the glade libraries, python, and the pygtk modules.

yorick -batch make.i
make
make check
make install


The install puts spydr.i in Y_SITE/i, the mouse_nowait.so library in
Y_HOME/lib and the spydr_start.i in Y_SITE/i-start. It also puts
the spydr.conf file in /etc and a spydr executable in /usr/local/bin

